    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-14T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-14T05:00:00-05:00" n="1089"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1089">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7–1449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-14T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 14, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 14—10:58 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1525. Re Shanghai’s 2667, July 8 to Dept,<note n="36" xml:id="d1089fn36">Not
                        printed.</note> repeated EmbOff Canton 864. We concur with recommendation in
                    Shanghai’s reference telegram that we should make representations against
                    Nationalist air attacks on Shanghai and other large population centers not only
                    because <pb facs="1131" n="1121" xml:id="pg_1121"/> of inflammation of
                    anti-American sentiment but also on humanitarian grounds and because of their
                    doubtful military utility in any case. We recall that representations to Chinese
                    Government last November re Nationalist bombing of Mukden seemed to have some
                    effect, though representations were limited to concern over American lives and
                    property Mukden.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 1525, repeated Shanghai 856, EmbOff Canton 637.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
